  </div>
  <div class="faq-item">
    <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="how-often-should-a-local-business-post-on-instagra">
      <span class="faq-q-text">How often should a local business post on Instagram?</span>
      <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
    </button>
    <div class="faq-a" id="how-often-should-a-local-business-post-on-instagra"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>3-4 posts per week is the sweet spot for most local businesses. This includes a mix of Reels, carousels, photos, and Stories. Consistency matters more than frequency. Posting 3 times per week every week outperforms posting 7 times 1 week and then nothing for 2 weeks.</p></div></div>
  </div>
  <div class="faq-item">
    <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="do-hashtags-still-work-on-instagram-in-2026">
      <span class="faq-q-text">Do hashtags still work on Instagram in 2026?</span>
      <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
    </button>
    <div class="faq-a" id="do-hashtags-still-work-on-instagram-in-2026"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Yes. Hashtags help your content appear in search results and on the Explore page. Use 5-15 hashtags per post with a mix of local, industry, and niche tags. Avoid using 30 hashtags or spamming irrelevant tags, as this can reduce your reach.</p></div></div>
  </div>
  <div class="faq-item">
    <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="is-instagram-better-than-facebook-for-local-busine">
