      <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
    </button>
    <div class="faq-a" id="how-much-should-a-local-business-spend-on-instagra"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Start with $150-300 per month by boosting your best-performing organic posts. Target a 10-25 mile radius around your business. You can scale up once you see which posts and audiences convert. Many local businesses see positive ROI at $10-15 per day.</p></div></div>
  </div>
  <div class="faq-item">
    <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="what-type-of-instagram-content-works-best-for-loca">
      <span class="faq-q-text">What type of Instagram content works best for local businesses?</span>
      <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
    </button>
    <div class="faq-a" id="what-type-of-instagram-content-works-best-for-loca"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Reels get the most reach (3-5x more than static posts). Carousels get the most saves. Stories keep you visible daily. The best strategy combines all 3 formats. Focus 40% of your content on showcasing your work and behind-the-scenes moments, 25% on educational tips, 20% on social proof, and 15% on promotions.</p></div></div>
  </div>
  <div class="faq-item">
    <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="can-instagram-replace-a-website-for-a-local-busine">
      <span class="faq-q-text">Can Instagram replace a website for a local business?</span>
      <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
    </button>
    <div class="faq-a" id="can-instagram-replace-a-website-for-a-local-busine"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>No. Instagram is a discovery and engagement platform, not a replacement for a website. You do not own your Instagram audience. The algorithm can change, and your reach can drop overnight. Use Instagram to drive traffic to your website, where you control the experience and capture leads directly.</p></div></div>
